      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 112565,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        1000004
      ],
      "solution": "<p>This man is suffering from tetanus, caused by the exotoxin produced by Clostridium tetani. This is a ubiquitous organism found widely in the soil. Although most people are immunized against tetanus, immunity is not lifelong and requires periodic booster immunizations. Tetanospasmin produced by C. tetani prevents the release of inhibitory neurotransmitters by cleaving synaptobrevins in synaptic vesicles. The effect of this toxin is a systemic, spastic paralysis that can result in death if not aggressively treated with antitoxin.</p>",
